ocative commentary on the human relationship to the larger world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aEnvironmental healthxHistoryxCalifornia. 0aEnvironmental healthzCaliforniaxHistory. 0aMedical geographyxHistoryxCalifornia. 0aMedical geographyzCaliforniaxHistory. 0aPublic healthxHistoryxCalifornia. 0aPublic healthzCaliforniaxHistory. 7aHISTORY / Modern / 20th Century.2bisacsh  a19th century.  a20th century.  abiomedicine.  acalifornia.  acancer clusters.  acauses of disease.  acentral valley.  adisease history.  aecologists.  aecology.  aecosystem.  aenvironment and culture.  aenvironmental history.  aenvironmental impact.  aenvironmental movement.  aenvironmental protest.  aenvironmentalists.  agerm theory.  ahuman impact.  aillness.  anatural science.  anatural world.  anonfiction.  apollution.  apublic health.  aregional ecology.  atextbooks.  atoxic chemicals.  awilderness.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093999840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520939998423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520939998/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles